    <title>Henry Cavill is reportedly out as DC’s Superman</title>
    <content type="html">  
    &lt;img alt="&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tc03oVLWJiTOyNY08m9F93jU9Ww=/0x0:6048x4032/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/61347433/BvSFaceoff.0.0.jpg" /&gt;



  &lt;p id="zC5mwT"&gt;Henry Cavill’s time playing the Man of Steel may be coming to an end. According to &lt;a href="https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/henry-cavill-as-superman-warner-bros-dc-universe-shake-up-1142306"&gt;a report from &lt;em&gt;The Hollywood Reporter&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the actor will be hanging up his cape after contract talks over a &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2018/7/21/17598148/shazam-dc-comics-warner-bros-trailer-watch-san-diego-comic-con"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Shazam!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Superman cameo fell through.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="85y0gw"&gt;According to &lt;em&gt;THR&lt;/em&gt;’s sources, Warner Bros. isn’t planning to make a &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2016/8/8/12403942/man-of-steel-two-superman-sequel-development"&gt;standalone Superman film&lt;/a&gt; for several years; instead, it’ll be focusing on a &lt;a href="https://deadline.com/2018/08/supergirl-movie-warner-bros-dc-comics-universe-oren-uziel-script-superman-1202440687/"&gt;recently announced Supergirl film&lt;/a&gt; as the studio attempts to refocus its struggling superhero franchise. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="24fKUq"&gt;“Superman is like James Bond, and after a certain run you have to look at new actors,” a studio source reportedly commented. This could indicate that DC and Warner Bros. are planning to move away from the overarching, connected storytelling that comic book rival Marvel has...&lt;/p&gt;
